Adding georefernced layer to a map

Once youve georeferenced an image, you can add it to a ggplot map as a raster layer.

Required packages

This example uses the following packages

library(tidyverse)
library(sf)
library(here)
library(raster)
library(ggspatial)
library(rnaturalearth)

Load the image as a raster object

First you will need to use the stack() function to read the image file as a RasterStack.

africa <- here("a3-files",
                 "large-image-files",
                 "africa_modified.tif") %>%
  stack()

Adding the image to a ggplot

Then you can use the layer_spatial() function from the ggspatial package to add the raster layer to a ggplot.

ggplot() +
  layer_spatial(africa)

Adding a vector layer

Now you can add some vector layers over the map image. Here, Ill add modern national borders

countries <- ne_countries(continent = "Africa",
                          returnclass = "sf") 


ggplot() +
  layer_spatial(africa) +
  geom_sf(data = countries,
          fill = NA,
          color = "black",
          size = 1)
